ssionals, offering pet care....\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Gastonia\",\"addressRegion\":\"NC\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"},\"image\":\"/images/parks/northcarolina/poston-park-river-trail/poston-park-river-trail-1.jpg\"}},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":10,\"item\":{\"@type\":\"SportsActivityLocation\",\"@id\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/avoncatawba-creeks-greenway\",\"name\":\"Avon/Catawba Creeks Greenway\",\"url\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/parks/avoncatawba-creeks-greenway\",\"description\":\"Avon/Catawba Creeks Greenway has become the premier destination for Gastonia dog owners. This facility features heated areas for cooler winters, knowledgeable animal handlers, offering pet care....\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Gastonia\",\"addressRegion\":\"NC\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"},\"image\":\"/images/parks/northcarolina/avon-catawba-creeks-greenway/avon-catawba-creeks-greenway-1.jpg\"}}]}25:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2d\"}}]\n2e:T49c,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I hike with my dog near Gastonia?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Crowders Mountain State Park is the jewel of the area. The trails range from moderate to strenuous, offering incredible views. Dogs must be on a leash at all times.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is there a dog park in Gastonia?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes, the Goat Island Park (in nearby Cramerton) and Lineberger Park offer great outdoor spaces. Bradley Station Dog Park in downtown Gastonia is a convenient urban option.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Can I take my dog to the Whitewater Center?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The U.S. National Whitewater Center is very dog-friendly, allowing leashed dogs on its extensive trail network. It’s a fantastic spot for active dogs and owners.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the leash laws in Gaston County?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Gaston County requires dogs to be under physical restraint (leash) or under the direct control of a competent person when off the owner’s property.\"}}]}26:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2e\"}}]\n27:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Dog Parks Directory\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Gastonia\\\"}]}\"}}]\n28:[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"variant\":\"light\"}]\n29:[\"$\",\"$L2f\",null,{\"items\":[{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"title\":\"City Overview\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-insights\",\"title\":\"Quick Facts\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-comparison\",\"title\":\"Top Comparisons\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-collections\",\"title\":\"Park Collections\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"neighborhood-clusters\",\"title\":\"Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-types-guide\",\"title\":\"Park Type Guide\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"title\":\"Map & Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"planning-essentials\",\"title\":\"Planning Essentials\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"expert-tips\",\"title\":\"Expert Advice\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-directory\",\"title\":\"Full Directory\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"owner-cta\",\"title\":\"Owner & Franchise\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"faq-section\",\"title\":\"FAQs\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"related-resources\",\"title\":\"More Resources\",\"level\":1}]}]\n2a:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"city-page-layout\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-button\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-trigger\",\"targetSelector\":\".table-of-contents\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-ul\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Contents\"}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"className\":\"city-hero-section \",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell city-hero-shell\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-hero-copy\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-breadcrumbs\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks Directory\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"Gastonia\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-eyebrow\",\"children\":\"Gateway to Adventure\"}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"children\":\"Gastonia Getaways\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-chip-row\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"hero-chip\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-label\",\"children\":\"State Park\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-value\",\"children\":\"1\"}],\"$undefined\"]}],[\"$\",\"div\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"hero-chip\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-label\",\"children\":\"Dog Parks\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-value\",\"children\":\"2\"}],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-description\",\"children\":\"Gastonia puts you at the doorstep of real adventure. With Crowders Mountain State Park minutes away, it is the perfect base camp for hiking dogs, while the city itself offers great parks and greenways.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-rich-description\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Gastonia, North Carolina, serves as the perfect launchpad for dogs with an adventurous spirit. Dominating the landscape is \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.ncparks.gov/state-parks/crowders-mountain-state-park\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"Crowders Mountain State Park\"}],null,\", a premier hiking destination that offers challenging trails and breathtaking views. For dog owners who love to hike, this is an invaluable resource right in their backyard. The trails vary in difficulty, allowing for everything from a strenuous summit climb to a pleasant woodland walk. It demands a leash, but the sensory experience for a dog—new scents, wildlife, and terrain—is unbeatable.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Within the city limits, Gastonia has modernized its pet amenities with facilities like the Bradley Station Dog Park. Located near the historic downtown, it provides a convenient, fenced space for urban residents to let their dogs play. The Avon Creek Greenway offers a more linear experience, connecting neighborhoods with green corridors ideal for daily leashed walks. The revitalization of the FUSE District is also bringing new energy to the town, with more pedestrian-friendly spaces emerging. Whether you are scaling a mountain peak or just enjoying a quiet evening at the park, Gastonia offers a diverse range of \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"experiences for you and your pet\"}],null,\".\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta-row\",\"children\